A compiler with support for C++11 is required,
for example GCC >= 4.7.

To compile and test PAMHD change the variable
ENVIRONMENT_MAKEFILE in Makefile in this directory
to point to the correct environment-specific makefile
or create your own. Then run make from the top level
directory, tests will be executed automatically.


Installing dependencies

Start from your home directory:
cd

Download required software:
git clone git://gitorious.org/dccrg/dccrg.git --branch c++11
git clone https://github.com/nasailja/gensimcell.git
git clone https://github.com/louisdx/cxx-prettyprint.git
wget http://www.open-mpi.org/software/ompi/v1.8/downloads/openmpi-1.8.1.tar.bz2
wget http://bitbucket.org/eigen/eigen/get/3.2.2.tar.bz2
wget "https://doc-0o-58-docs.googleusercontent.com/docs/securesc/ha0ro937gcuc7l7deffksulhg5h7mbp1/eu9dujp4cu4mumar7uh3jrif0lltqh6g/1407261600000/10606444718388524723/*/0BzuB-ydOOoduNkU4STZxeWJLLTA?h=16653014193614665626&e=download" -O muparserx_v3_0_3.zip

Install Open-MPI:
tar xf openmpi-1.8.1.tar.bz2
cd openmpi-1.8.1
CC=gcc-mp-4.8 CXX=g++-mp-4.8 FC=gfortran-mp-4.8 ./configure --prefix=$HOME
make
make install
cd ..
rm -rf openmpi-1.8.1

Install Eigen:
tar xf 3.2.2.tar.bz2
mv eigen-eigen-1306d75b4a21/Eigen $HOME/include
rm -rf eigen-eigen-1306d75b4a21/

Install muparserx:
unzip muparserx_v3_0_3.zip
make -C muparserx_v3_0_3 CC=g++-mp-4.8
mv muparserx_v3_0_3/bin/libmuparserx.a $HOME/lib
cp muparserx_v3_0_3/parser/*.h $HOME/include
rm -rf muparserx_v3_0_3


Installation of boost and zoltan is detailed at:
https://gitorious.org/dccrg/pages/Install
